ow-To Guides                Digital Scholarship Hub: Home     Welcome to the Digital Scholarship Research Hub!  The UIC Library "Hub" are facilities that are available to support digital scholarship/humanities experimental research and instruction.  The "Hub" provides technology, data and individual consultations and expertise to support creative, innovative and non-traditional research, development. Hubs provide ubiquitous access to resources and expertise to help UIC faculty, staff and students experiment, collaborate and create in physical, virtual, 2-, and 3- dimensional environments.  There are two "Hubs" located at the Richard J Daley Library.  You can schedule consultations, reserve equipment, or explore the availability of our resources and tools using these links.      Hours  Monday - Friday   10 am - 5 pm                   Hub 1 (Daley Library 1-461)      Hub 1 (Room 1-461)  Resources are available to UIC Faculty, staff and students                3D Printing      3D Scanning      Laser Cutting      Material Cutting      Sewing Machine      Large Format Printing     CNC Milling Machine                      Hub 2 (Daley Library 2-460)      Hub 2 (Room 2-460)  Resources are available to UIC faculty, staff and students                Modeling    Graphics      Video Editing     Audio Editing      Video Equipment      Programming      Multi-Monitor Visualization      Data Visualization      Augmented Reality      Text/Data Mining      Data Analysis                    Scholars At Work                             Next: Resources >>        Last Updated:  Apr 20, 2020 1:29 PM    URL:  https://researchguides.uic.edu/hub    Print Page     Staff Login        Subjects:  Data Management , Digital Scholarship                     Logo for the University of Illinois at Chicago       University  Library          Locations          Richard J. Daley Library    801 S. Morgan   Chicago , IL  60607       Phone  (312) 996-2724              Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  